cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of single image super resolution, which is a common computer vision problem. The use of the squeeze and excitation module also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The recursive structure and progressive reconstruction method may also indicate that it could be classified under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation on benchmark test sets suggests that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
